Sentencas: The sol-gel method was adopted to synthesize novel cobalt and strontium-free Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-delta (x = 0 and 0.2, abbreviated as PBF and PBFN) perovskite oxides.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was aimed to discuss the influence of B-site Ni substitution on structure and electrochemical properties of Pr0.5Ba0.5FeO3-delta.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicated that PBF-based oxides were both cubic perovskite structure.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ni atoms were successfully doped into the B sites of PBF, resulting in lattice shrinkage.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ni doping could enhance the oxygen reduction activity by increasing the surface oxygen content and the release of lattice oxygen to increase oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 700 degrees C, the cathodic polarization resistance of PBFN (0.0726 omega center dot cm(2)) was lower than PBF (0.122 omega center dot cm(2)), and the maximum power density (PPD) of PBFN (528.79 mW center dot cm(-2)) was higher than PBF (259.65 mW center dot cm(-2)).
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After 80 h polarization, the open-circuit voltage did not change significantly.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, PBFN has the potential to be more suitable cathode material of IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Novel cobalt and strontium-free perovskite Pr0.5Ba0.5Fe1-xNixO3-δ (x=0 and 0.2) as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
